<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870327-0084 </DOCNO><HL> R.L. Polk Raises Its StakeIn Wiland Services to 20.4%</HL><DD> 03/27/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WSVSTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   R.L. Polk andamp; Co., a Detroit-based marketing firm, said it raised its 19% stake in Wiland Services Inc. to 20.4% of the common shares outstanding.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, Polk said it holds 725,603 Wiland common shares, including 50,000 shares purchased in an open-market transaction at $2.25 each. The date of the purchase wasn't provided.    A spokesman for Wiland, a Boulder, Colo.-based direct-mail marketing concern, said the company believes the purchase is for investment purposes, as the filing indicated. Polk currently has one representative on Wiland's six-member board of directors. </TEXT></DOC>